title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: The supply function continued to ensure availability of goods and services required for effective programme implementation during the year. The total supplies and services received valued at $127,514,195. These includes procurement services under global fund project Scaling up prevention and control of Malaria in Sudan, Resilient and Sustainable Systems for Health and Immunization services supported by Gavi and institutional services including construction of schools, child friendly facilities and rehabilitation of government warehouses and regular sectoral program. The total dispatch of the program supplies from UNICEF controlled warehouses stands at $28,089,700 representing 63% of the total purchases of program funded supplies. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/01/2022
